# Public `docs/` policy

GitHub `docs/` is **player- and packager-facing only**. Allowed tracked files:

- `docs/user-manual.md`
- `docs/options-guide.md`
- `docs/fdroid.md`
- `docs/FDROID_README.md`

`docs/FDROID_APPLY.md` may exist locally (gitignored); do not force-add it.

## Never put in `docs/` (and never `git add` them)

- Internal AI / agent plans, pause notes, architecture edit maps
- Audits, UX reviews, roadmaps, release drafts, follow-up feedback
- Polish working notes meant for the team only
- Feature design plans (`*PLAN*`, `*_PLAN.md`, mapper reviews, GMCP manager plans, etc.)

If you need a written plan or audit, put it **outside the repo** (e.g. `~/Coding/blowtorch-private-docs/`) or in chat. Do **not** create new markdown under `docs/` unless the user explicitly asks to update one of the four public guides above.

## When documenting a feature for players

Update `user-manual.md` and/or `options-guide.md` in English. Do not add a parallel “plan” file in `docs/`.
